132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 280
S.P. 130 In Senate, January 28, 2025
An Act to Establish Lifetime Ferry Passes for Retired Maine State
Ferry Service Employees
Reference to the Committee on Transportation suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BEEBE-CENTER of Knox.
Cosponsored by Senator: CURRY of Waldo.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 23 MRSA §4408 is enacted to read:
3 §4408. Lifetime ferry passes for retired ferry service employees
4 A state employee as defined in Title 5, section 17001, subsection 40 who is retired from
5 employment with the Maine State Ferry Service is eligible to receive a lifetime ferry pass
6 and a waiver from any reservation fees. For the purposes of this section, "lifetime ferry
7 pass" means a pass that provides, on a ferry operated by the Maine State Ferry Service, 2
8 round-trip passages per month for a passenger and a vehicle if the passenger gives at least
9 24 hours' notice of a planned round-trip passage to the Maine State Ferry Service.
10 SUMMARY
1111 This bill provides that a state employee who is retired from employment with the Maine
1122 State Ferry Service is eligible to receive a lifetime ferry pass and a waiver from any
1133 reservation fees. The bill defines "lifetime ferry pass" as a pass that provides 2 round-trip
1144 passages per month for a passenger and a vehicle on a ferry operated by the Maine State
1155 Ferry Service if the passenger gives at least 24 hours' notice of a planned round-trip passage
1166 to the Maine State Ferry Service.
